The paper deals with the problem of moving an autonomous agent through an unknown environment, which is a crucial problem for robotics and network analysis. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and perception of the explorer, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of advice complexity, which is a topic in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the five most likely categories for this paper.
